      "inputs": [],
      "title": "Quick Presets + Safe Experiment Order",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Known-good presets\n- **Fast test:** 640×352, 20 fps, 3 seconds, 40 steps\n- **Baseline:** 640×352, 24 fps, 3 seconds, 40 steps\n- **Higher resolution:** 832×480, 24 fps, 3 seconds, 40 steps\n\nEnter **FPS + total seconds**. The node calculates the closest valid LingBot frame count automatically (20 fps × 3 sec → 61 frames; 24 fps × 3 sec → 73 frames).\n\n## Experiment cleanly\n1. Keep the seed fixed.\n2. Change one setting at a time.\n3. Try steps, then CFG, then shift.\n4. Change resolution/duration last because they affect render time most.\n\nVerified baseline: **CFG 3.0 / shift 3.0 / 40 steps / Sage**."
      ],
      "color": "#5b4615",
      "bgcolor": "#372b0e"
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        650,
        700
      ],
      "size": [
        570,
        300
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 12,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "title": "How Progress Is Reported",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Five visible stages\n1. **Load Model** — file validation, transformer, VAE/scheduler\n2. **Encode Prompt** — JSON validation, Qwen load/encode/evict\n3. **Denoise** — exact `step / total`, percent, elapsed, and ETA\n4. **VAE Decode** — latent video to RGB frames\n5. **Encode + Save** — Video Helper Suite frame progress\n\nThe active node is outlined by ComfyUI. LingBot nodes also display multiline live status directly on the node. Console logs remain available for deeper diagnostics."
      ],
      "color": "#243447",
      "bgcolor": "#182433"
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        1260,
        700
      ],
      "size": [
        570,
        300
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 13,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "title": "Prompt Rules (Important)",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Plaintext is now supported\nWrite normal prose in the first prompt box. The installed local Qwen3-VL model expands it, maps it to LingBot's full JSON schema, validates timestamps/required fields, repairs once if needed, then encodes it — all from one Qwen load.\n\nThe second box is an optional structured-JSON override for advanced use. Leave it empty for plaintext mode. The generated caption and JSON appear in the preview node.\n\nLeave negative prompt empty to use LingBot's vendored default JSON."
      ],
      "color": "#4b2a2a",
      "bgcolor": "#301b1b"
    }
